<div class="unit-20">&nbsp;</div>
<div class="unit-60"><h2>Locations and situations</h2>
  <h3>On the interaction of negation and finiteness in Avar</h3>
</div>
</div>
<div class="units-row">		
<div class="unit-20 dateblock"><h4>7 February 2015</h4>

  <p class="conference-description">TiN-Dag,  Utrecht University.</p>

  <p><a href="http://pavelrudnev.github.io/pdf/tindag2015-handout.pdf" class="badge"><i class="fa fa-file-pdf-o"></i>&nbsp;download handout</a></p>
</div>
<div class="unit-60">

<p>In this talk I discuss a number of restrictions on sentential negation marking in Avar, a Northeast Caucasian language, and sketch a tentative analysis of the observed morphosyntactic facts as having a semantic basis. The two different negation markers (<em>-ro</em> and <em>-ƒç'o</em>) are analysed, based on the proposal in Ramchand & Svenonius 2014, as taking complements of a different syntactic size and semantic type.</p>

		<p><b>Keywords:</b> syntax, semantics, negation, nominalization, event semantics, situation semantics, Avar</p> 


</div>
	
</div>
</div>

</div>





